Sentencas: A layered perovskite electrode material, La0.6Sr1.4MnO4+delta (LSMO4), has been studied for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SSOFCs) on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte.
Titulo: The performance of La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 layered perovskite electrode material for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The chemical compatibility tests indicate that no reaction occurred between LSMO4 oxide and LSGM electrolyte at temperature up to 1000 degrees C both in air and 5% H-2.
Titulo: The performance of La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 layered perovskite electrode material for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lower conductivity in 5% H-2 and higher conduction activation energy than those in air would be caused by poorer overlap of both sigma and pi bonds.
Titulo: The performance of La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 layered perovskite electrode material for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: DFT + U calculations also show that oxygen vacancies which formed in reducing atmosphere may block the 3D hopping path for electrons or holes through Mn-O-Mn chains.
Titulo: The performance of La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 layered perovskite electrode material for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For LSMO4 electrode, SEM results indicate that the electrode formed good contact with the electrolyte after being sintered at 900 degrees C for 2 h. At 800 degrees C, the polarization resistance of the LSMO4 cathode is about 0.87 Omega cm(2) in air, while the polarization resistance of the LSMO4 anode is about 2.07 Omega cm(2) in 5% H-2.
Titulo: The performance of La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 layered perovskite electrode material for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LSMO4 exhibits better electrochemical activity for oxygen reduction than that for hydrogen oxidation.
Titulo: The performance of La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 layered perovskite electrode material for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A cell with LSGM electrolyte, LSMO4-LSGM mixture as anode and cathode simultaneously displays a maximum power density of 59 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. (C) 2014
Titulo: The performance of La0.6Sr1.4MnO4 layered perovskite electrode material for intermediate temperature symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
